.TH "i40e_aq_add_mirrorrule" 9 "i40e_aq_add_mirrorrule" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_aq_add_mirrorrule \- add a mirror rule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "i40e_status" i40e_aq_add_mirrorrule
.BI "(struct i40e_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 sw_seid "  ","
.BI "u16 rule_type "  ","
.BI "u16 dest_vsi "  ","
.BI "u16 count "  ","
.BI "__le16 *mr_list "  ","
.BI "struct i40e_asq_cmd_details *cmd_details "  ","
.BI "u16 *rule_id "  ","
.BI "u16 *rules_used "  ","
.BI "u16 *rules_free "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the hw struct
.IP "sw_seid" 12
Switch SEID (to which rule refers)
.IP "rule_type" 12
Rule Type (ingress/egress/VLAN)
.IP "dest_vsi" 12
SEID of VSI to which packets will be mirrored
.IP "count" 12
length of the list
.IP "mr_list" 12
list of mirrored VSI SEIDs or VLAN IDs
.IP "cmd_details" 12
pointer to command details structure or NULL
.IP "rule_id" 12
Rule ID returned from FW
.IP "rules_used" 12
Number of rules used in internal switch
.IP "rules_free" 12
Number of rules free in internal switch
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add mirror rule. Mirror rules are supported for VEBs or VEPA elements only
